"Calebasse" is an Ivoirian's game. It is played by 2 or more players. Each player has colored beans (one color per player).
Every round, players bet a quantity of beans by putting them in the "Calebasse". Then somebody pick randomly a bean in the Calebasse. And the color determins the winner who gets all the beans in the "Calebasse". He paints them with his color. And a other round can start. 

